    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>The examples use association lists with explicit semiring operations. Kidney and Wu work with free semimodule monads in Haskell, using type classes to abstract over the semiring. The counting example above uses an explicit loop with <code>set-cdr!</code> to merge duplicates; in the paper, that merge is the free semimodule's universal property — the unique algebra morphism that folds a formal sum into a concrete semiring value. The computation is the same; the universality guarantee is not.</p>
    <p>Every example is <strong class="text-green-400">Simplified</strong>.</p>

